\text{Number of pages} = \frac{2000 \text{ cents}}{2.5 \text{ cents/page}} = 800 \text{ pages}
\] Therefore, the number of pages that can be copied for $20 is \(\boxed{800}\). </think> <answer> 800 </answer>

